---

NOTE on generated content: voicepipe builds fine-tuning datasets and models in
the voice of whatever corpus you point it at. The corpus you supply, the
dataset it produces, and the model it trains are yours and your responsibility
— including any content, licensing, or policy obligations attached to the
source material. The bundled `character` project template ships content rules
(no slurs; no attributing villainy to whole groups; no out-of-era references;
no AI-acknowledgment) as sensible defaults for both synthesis and the deployed
model's moderation layer, but enforcing them is on you.
